title: Design Coordination Meeting
description: Design coordination meeting to close outstanding design items ahead of the IFC package freeze.
summary: Facilitator: John Jones (Design Manager) Attendees: Emma Lawson (Architect), Raj Patel (Structural Engineer), Lisa Wong (Services Engineer), Mark Jensen (Contractor Rep), Sophie Grant (Quantity Surveyor)  1. Welcome & Purpose • Objective: close outstanding design items ahead of the IFC package freeze.  2. Architectural Updates • Façade rhythm revision – bay width increased 3m → 3.3m; mock-ups accepted. • Stair-core optimisation – 150mm wall-thickness reduction adds ≈ 5m² NLA per floor. • Interior finishes – lobby stone and carpet tile selections endorsed.  Actions: - Issue Rev D GA drawings and updated façade schedule by 02 Aug 2025 - Incorporate stair-core reduction and finishes into model by 12 Aug 2025  3. Structural Coordination • Transfer beam – 900mm-deep, 50MPa beam clears services zone by 75mm. • Wet-area set-downs – 40mm recess standardised; waterproofing warranty confirmed. • Seismic restraint – Category B building importance; no extra façade bracing required.  Actions: - Provide preliminary transfer-beam shop drawings by 05 Aug 2025 - Confirm procurement lead-time for 50MPa concrete mix by 06 Aug 2025  4. Building Services (MEP) • Riser consolidation – data & small-power risers merged (lvls 8–12), eliminating one shaft. • HVAC diffuser clashes – diffusers to shift 150mm to clear new mullions. • Fire-sprinkler layout – 12 heads clash with pendant lights; rerouting required.  Actions: - Update MEP model and re-issue by 04 Aug 2025  5. Digital / BIM Coordination • Navisworks federation updated (Arch Rev D draft, Struct Rev C, MEP Rev B). • Clash matrix: 27 high-priority clashes remain (down from 61). • Decision: activate ACC Design Collaboration for real-time model sharing.  Actions: - Upload clash-free federated model to ACC Design Collaboration workspace by 03 Aug 2025

title: Untitled meeting Jul 26, 2025 1:01 PM
description: Design Coordination meeting via Microsoft Teams facilitated by John Jones (Design Manager). Attendees: Emma Lawson (Architect), Raj Patel (Structural Engineer), Lisa Wong (Services Engineer), Mark Jensen (Contractor Rep), Sophie Grant (Quantity Surveyor). The purpose of the meeting is to close outstanding design items ahead of the IFC package freeze and record actions for the ACC action tracker.
